  "original_title": "\u0da2\u0db1\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2\u0db0\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dba \u0db4\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0db4\u0dca\u0db4\u0dcf\u0da9\u0dd4 \u0dc0\u0dd3 \u0d87\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0db6\u0dc0 \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dda\u0daf\u0db1\u0dba \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db8 \u0dc4\u0dd9\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Announcing that the presidency is vacant tomorrow",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to the Constitution and Section 4 of the Election of the President (Special Provisions) Act No. 2 of 1981, the Parliament is scheduled to meet tomorrow (16) Saturday at 10.00 am, the Secretary General of the Parliament Mr. Dhammika Dasanayake informs all members.",
        "According to Section 4 of the Election of the President (Special Provisions) Act No. 2 of 1981, the Parliament must be convened within three days of the vacancy in the presidency.",
        "Thus, the Secretary General is scheduled to announce tomorrow (16) that there is a vacancy in the office of the President according to Section 5 of the Act.",
        "Meanwhile, at the party leader and parliamentary affairs committee meeting today at 10.00 am, the speaker Mr. Mahinda Yapa Abeywardena informed that the new president will be elected by the parliament on the 20th as previously decided by the party leaders.",
        "Accordingly, the speaker said that nominations will be called on Tuesday 19th and after that, a member of Parliament will be selected for the presidency after the voting held in Parliament on Wednesday 20th."
      ],
